						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>Mallidēva 13th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription refers itself to the reign of Mallidēva year 10, Vyaya, Kārttika ba. 14, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>This nishidhige stone records the observance of the vow of <hi rend="italic">sanyasana</hi> and death by <hi rend="italic">samādhi</hi> of Kāḷigāvuṇḍi, a lay-disciple of Dharmasēna.</p>						

						</summary>
